🧠 PROBLEM JO REACT SOLVE KARNA CHAHTA THA

Normal JS me ye dekho:

function Component() {
  let count = 0;

  function increment() {
    count++;
    console.log(count);
  }

  increment();
  increment();
}


❌ Problem:

Component dobara render hua

count firse 0

State RESET 😡

👉 React ko data YAAD rakhna tha renders ke beech

🔥 AB SOCH: REACT KYA CHAHTA THA?

React chahta tha:

count private ho

render ke baad bhi zinda rahe

sirf setCount se change ho

har component ka apna state ho

👉 Ye sab bina closure IMPOSSIBLE hai

🧠 useState ka SIMPLE MENTAL MODEL (REAL)

Soch useState internally kuch aisa karta hai (simplified):

function useState(initialValue) {
  let state = initialValue;

  function setState(newValue) {
    state = newValue;
    rerender();
  }

  return [state, setState];
}


🚨 IMPORTANT:
state ek local variable hai
setState usko YAAD rakhta hai

👉 YE HI CLOSURE HAI

🔍 Ab step-by-step breakdown
1️⃣ First render
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);


state = 0

setState ban gaya

setState ne state ko pakad liya

2️⃣ Button click
setCount(count + 1);


setState call hua

Wo apne closure se state access karta

state = 1

React re-render karta

3️⃣ Re-render hota hai

Component function firse chalta hai
BUT ❗

👉 setState purana hi hota hai
👉 aur wo old state ko yaad rakhta hai

Isliye:

count === 1

💣 SABSE IMPORTANT LINE (YAHIN CLICK HOGA)

Component function re-run hota hai,
par useState ka closure re-create nahi hota

Bas.
Isi line me poora React band hai.

🔥 handleClick me closure ka role
function Component() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  function handleClick() {
    setCount(count + 1);
  }
}


❓ handleClick ko count kaise mil raha?

👉 Closure

handleClick:

component ke scope me bana

count ko pakad ke rakha

⚠️ Ab ek REAL BUG jo closure ki wajah se aata hai
setTimeout(() => {
  setCount(count + 1);
}, 1000);


❌ Bug:

count OLD value ka ho jaata hai

kyunki closure purana count pakad ke baitha

✅ Correct way
setCount(prev => prev + 1);


❓ Kyun kaam karta?
👉 Kyunki React latest state inject karta, closure pe depend nahi karta

🧠 useState ko ONE LINE me samjho

useState ek function hai jo ek variable ko closure me lock kar deta hai
taaki re-render ke baad bhi value zinda rahe

Bas. Aur kuch nahi.

